reviews.reviewText: A wonderful game for small children, my grandchildren who are 2.5-3 years old love it very much, I purchased 2 sets, the size is excellent, the cubes are safe, light, the colors are great and the quantity is enough for everyone

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fun spatial reasoning building toys
reviews.reviewText: My 5 year old son loved these so much he tried to steal some from school. I surprised him with some of his own (2 kits) on a rainy camping trip and we played for hours. You can build complex structures with these, so don't let the simple, obvious ideas fool you. I wish we had these years ago. Yes, these are fun for younger kids too, but you do have to be pretty spatially aware of the shapes and how the forces can be used to build complex things with them. These things were called Wedgits at his school, but these are the same as those, just different manufacturer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was a gift for a two year old and the mother said it is now her go to gift for two year olds. A two year can quickly use these blocks without frustration. She observed her child figuring out how to build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars My 2.5 yr old LOVES these!
reviews.reviewText: We gave these to my 2.5 yr old son for Easter and he absolutely loves stacking these. They are so light and easy for him to stack and play with. He has spent hours in the last few days enjoying these. It does say for 2-5 yr olds but I would not recommend giving them to a 2 yr old. The smallest orange block is very easy for a child to put in their mouth. My son immediately tried to put it in his mouth so I removed those from the set for the time being. The rest of the pieces are a great size for little hands. The colors are nice a bright. There are so many building options for these blocks and I love that it came with a book to give you ideas. Overall, I would definitely recommend for kids 3-5 or are out of the "Putting everything in their mouth stage."
